"attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John (William) Lovelace/Luvlaz was born in 1225, in England, United Kingdom, his father, A de Luvlaz, was 21 and his mother, Mrs A de Luvlaz, was 21. He had at least 1 son with Mrs John William Luvlaz."},"et":{"1225–":"1225–Surnud","1225–Male":"1225–Surnud","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1247–1270":"1247–1270","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1247":"1247","1270":"1270","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1225–":"1225–Kuollut","1225–Male":"1225–Kuollut","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1247–1270":"1247–1270","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1247":"1247","1270":"1270","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1225–":"1225–Décédé","1225–Male":"1225–Décédé","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","1247–1270":"1247–1270","1205–Male":"1205–Décédé","1205–Female":"1205–Décédée","1205":"1205","1225":"1225","1247":"1247","1270":"1270","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque John (William) Lovelace/Luvlaz est né en 1225, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, A de Luvlaz, avait 21 ans et sa mère, Mrs A de Luvlaz, avait 21 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs John William Luvlaz."},"de":{"1225–":"1225–Verstor